title: Boeing warns of reduced 737 Max production and deliveries due to parts issue
description: Boeing on Thursday warned of reduced 737 Max production and deliveries in the near term due to a parts issue originating with a supplier.

title: Amazon CEO Andy Jassy says 'really good' A.I. models take 'billions of dollars' to train
description: Amazon isn't the first to market with a model that generate human-like text. But Amazon wants to stand out with low prices, easy of use and choice.

title: Colombia launched a new digital nomad visa: Its best 3 cities for people who can work from anywhere
description: Colombia has launched a digital nomad visa that is designed primarily for entrepreneurs, freelancers or workers with the freedom to work from anywhere.

title: Arrest made in stabbing death of Cash App founder Bob Lee, men reportedly knew each other
description: San Francisco supervisor Aaron Peskin confirms that an arrest has been made, and a report by Mission Local says the men may have known each other.

title: Demand for luxury watches shows no sign of fading, says Audemars Piguet CEO
description: The luxury watch market has seen soaring secondary market prices, boosted by new demand from younger generations.

title: EU will issue fresh wave of sanctions to stop Russia reinventing their war machine, official says
description: The EU will launch an 11th wave of economic penalties on Russia and seek to crack down on efforts by the country to evade sanctions, a top EU official said.

title: England's top soccer clubs agree to ban gambling sponsors on front of matchday shirts
description: It follows years of campaigns against gambling ads in sport and as the Premier League seeks to show it can self-govern.

title: Old planes get stripped for parts while airlines wait on new jets
description: Aircraft parts are in high demand, and some companies are turning to used planes to get ready for a big summer travel season.

title: Chinese ride-hailing giant DiDi developing own driverless taxis, plans to roll them out in 2025
description: DiDi's autonomous driving unit showed off a concept robotaxi, or driverless taxi, called DiDi Neuron.

title: Amazon CEO Andy Jassy says in shareholder letter he's confident he can get costs under control
description: Amazon published CEO Andy Jassy's latest annual letter to shareholders.

title: From swimming pools to gardening, the rich's privileged lifestyles are driving urban water crises, study says
description: The study found that despite accounting for a small percentage of the population, the rich use over half of the water consumed in Cape Town.

title: UK economy flat in February as strikes and inflation bite — and the IMF delivers reality check
description: The U.K. economy flatlined in February as widespread industrial action and persistently high inflation stymied activity.

title: Twitter partners with eToro to let users trade stocks, crypto as Musk pushes app into finance
description: Starting Thursday, Twitter will give users the option to buy and sell stocks and other assets from eToro, the company told CNBC exclusively.

title: The cap on Russian oil is unlikely to change soon — despite opposing views on whether it’s working
description: The G-7, EU and Australia decided late last year to impose a cap of $60 a barrel on Russian oil in an effort to ratchet up the pressure on Moscow.

title: The 'energy crisis is solved' and the German economy is safe, Bundesbank's Nagel says
description: Germany's energy worries are over and Europe's largest economy has the "inherent strength" to recover, Bundesbank President Joachim Nagel says.

title: The yen could reach 120 per dollar, up 20% from October's peak
description: The Japanese yen could strengthen to 120 per dollar by the end of the year on the back of a potential BOJ policy tweak — or its total abolishment.

title: Billionaires are fascinated by solar geoengineering — but climate scientists are far from convinced
description: Hundreds of climate scientists are firmly against proliferating calls for solar geoengineering research and its potential development.

title: Warren Buffett's trip to Tokyo is seen as a 'stamp of approval' for investing in Japan
description: Buffett recently revealed that he raised his stakes in the country's top trading houses, saying he was "confounded" by the opportunity.

title: Young people in Greater China are blowing their paychecks every month — even if they don't have to
description: The young would rather give up on increasingly unattainable dreams like buying a house to spend on things they're "guaranteed to get today," one professor says.

title: Singapore rent prices are still sky-high. Long-time expats are having to consider drastic changes
description: Foreign expats in Singapore continue to feel the pain as home rental prices remain high and show little signs of returning to pre-pandemic levels.
